The paper deals with deep neural networks and their compression through pruning, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The focus on layer-wise pruning and the evaluation of the importance of each layer suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of pruning to achieve compact representations also relates to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper's application to image classification tasks suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
